name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: ipc.client.kill.max
description: Defines the maximum number of clients to disconnect in one go.

name: dfs.client.failover.connection.retries
description:
Expert only. Indicates the number of retries a failover IPC client
    will make to establish a server connection.

name: dfs.provided.aliasmap.inmemory.batch-size
description: The batch size when iterating over the database backing the aliasmap

name: ftp.stream-buffer-size
description:
The size of buffer to stream files.
  The size of this buffer should probably be a multiple of hardware
  page size (4096 on Intel x86), and it determines how much data is
  buffered during read and write operations.

name: mapreduce.shuffle.connection-keep-alive.timeout
description:
The number of seconds a shuffle client attempts to retain
   http connection. Refer "Keep-Alive: timeout=" header in
   Http specification

name: io.mapfile.bloom.size
description:
The size of BloomFilter-s used in BloomMapFile. Each time this many
  keys is appended the next BloomFilter will be created (inside a DynamicBloomFilter).
  Larger values minimize the number of filters, which slightly increases the performance,
  but may waste too much space if the total number of keys is usually much smaller
  than this number.
